1
00:00:19,740 --> 00:00:23,240
♪Hey, you, you, you,
why is it you again?♪

2
00:00:23,540 --> 00:00:27,570
♪Always stumbling upon
my little secrets♪

3
00:00:27,970 --> 00:00:31,990
♪Falling on my brows, my lashes,
even the strands by my mouth♪

4
00:00:31,990 --> 00:00:36,660
♪Like my favorite kitten
on a rainy spring afternoon♪

5
00:00:36,660 --> 00:00:41,320
♪Hey, you, you, you,
why is it you again?♪

6
00:00:41,320 --> 00:00:45,110
♪You effortlessly awaken
my protective instincts♪

7
00:00:45,390 --> 00:00:49,450
♪Hitting all my little thoughts,
my doubts, and my temper♪

8
00:00:49,730 --> 00:00:54,300
♪Like my favorite beer and fried chicken
in autumn, or spicy boiled fish in winter♪

9
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:58,770
♪Why is it you again?
That sweet way you speak♪

10
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:03,080
♪As if the whole world knows
my mind is full of you♪

11
00:01:03,360 --> 00:01:07,530
♪Why is it still you?
That secret smile behind your cool facade♪

12
00:01:07,730 --> 00:01:11,760
♪I might as well play along.
Let me protect you♪

13
00:01:12,060 --> 00:01:16,190
♪Why is it always you?
The smile at the corner of your lips♪

14
00:01:16,480 --> 00:01:20,590
♪Before I knew it, the words blurted out,
"I like you. I only like you."♪

15
00:01:29,530 --> 00:01:33,220
♪Before I knew it, the words blurted out,
"I like you. I only like you."♪

16
00:01:33,220 --> 00:01:34,040
=Love Has Fireworks=

17
00:01:34,040 --> 00:01:34,861
(Based on "Investment Men and Women"
by Hong Er on Jinjiang Literature City)

18
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,980
=Episode 7=

19
00:01:38,070 --> 00:01:39,680
Mr. Li, shall we?

20
00:01:40,040 --> 00:01:40,400
Sure.

21
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:41,150
Let's begin.

22
00:01:43,790 --> 00:01:45,070
As of the second quarter,

23
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:47,790
the Shanlifang Hotel Group's network

24
00:01:47,822 --> 00:01:50,644
(Shanlifang Hotel Group's Market Share)
includes 130 hotels in operation,

25
00:01:50,666 --> 00:01:52,244
(Shanlifang's Operations)
with over 30,000 rooms.

26
00:01:52,311 --> 00:01:54,920
It covers 24 provinces nationwide

27
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:57,760
and 53 cities in municipalities
and autonomous regions.

28
00:01:57,860 --> 00:01:58,870
(Landlady, Fang Yun used your report.)

29
00:01:58,870 --> 00:02:00,520
(There's hope for rehire.)
In addition, another 120 hotels

30
00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:01,577
are pending opening.

31
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:04,710
They are expected
to all open within five years.

32
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:06,590
Of course,

33
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,560
these promising prospects

34
00:02:08,888 --> 00:02:11,022
(Qian Fei: You're here.)
are where capital seeks profit.

35
00:02:11,111 --> 00:02:12,560
And our responsibility is

36
00:02:13,150 --> 00:02:14,340
to ensure it makes

37
00:02:14,340 --> 00:02:15,880
(In the meeting room. Treat me tonight.)
a perfect debut.

38
00:02:19,644 --> 00:02:22,220
(Qian Fei: Stop flattering yourself.
But order any dish you want.)

39
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:26,000
That concludes today's presentation.

40
00:02:28,430 --> 00:02:30,590
To facilitate future work,

41
00:02:30,710 --> 00:02:32,120
we've drafted

42
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:34,133
a responsibilities allocation agreement.

43
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:36,840
It's mainly to define

44
00:02:36,870 --> 00:02:39,800
our scope of work and responsibilities.

45
00:02:40,030 --> 00:02:40,870
Please take a look.

46
00:02:50,430 --> 00:02:51,120
Mr. Li.

47
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:53,520
Are you feeling unwell today?

48
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:54,150
Yes, sorry.

49
00:02:54,150 --> 00:02:55,840
My stomach's a bit upset.

50
00:02:56,030 --> 00:02:56,870
Zhao De,

51
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:58,400
have Legal review this later.

52
00:02:59,560 --> 00:03:01,710
We'll discuss it afterward, alright?

53
00:03:02,630 --> 00:03:03,870
I need to use the restroom.

54
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:17,960
Is your meeting over?

55
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:19,000
Why are you here?

56
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:20,030
No, no time.

57
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,030
Where's the restroom?

58
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:26,280
Turn left.

59
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:40,000
Boss.

60
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:41,520
Boss.

61
00:03:41,710 --> 00:03:42,910
Don't shout.

62
00:03:44,430 --> 00:03:45,470
The middle stall.

63
00:03:49,030 --> 00:03:50,080
You okay, Boss?

64
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:52,560
Anyone in the nearby stalls?

65
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:01,000
No.

66
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:04,120
Did you notice

67
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,520
something's fishy about this agreement?

68
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:08,960
Yes.

69
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:10,560
I've been wondering, too.

70
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:11,800
Why did Fang Yun

71
00:04:11,910 --> 00:04:14,155
suddenly come up
with this responsibility agreement?

72
00:04:15,030 --> 00:04:15,910
What's the catch?

73
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:19,680
It's my fault for mishandling this.

74
00:04:21,070 --> 00:04:22,360
The original plan

75
00:04:22,630 --> 00:04:23,777
was for Qian Fei to lay out

76
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,720
Shanlifang's issues
right in front of Fang Yun,

77
00:04:25,950 --> 00:04:28,070
so she couldn't keep
turning a blind eye.

78
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:31,120
But I didn't expect
Fang Yun to react so fast.

79
00:04:31,190 --> 00:04:32,480
She shifted the blame first.

80
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:36,390
Qian Fei is your weapon?

81
00:04:36,750 --> 00:04:37,720
Exactly.

82
00:04:38,160 --> 00:04:39,390
Almost killed myself with it.

83
00:04:43,270 --> 00:04:44,870
What did you eat last night, Boss?

84
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:46,630
Then what do we do now?

85
00:04:47,430 --> 00:04:49,560
Do we sign this agreement or not?

86
00:04:49,950 --> 00:04:51,430
Are you out of your mind?

87
00:04:51,830 --> 00:04:53,120
Of course we can't sign it.

88
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:54,190
Once we do,

89
00:04:54,270 --> 00:04:55,466
if Shanlifang goes public

90
00:04:55,470 --> 00:04:56,920
and there are any financial issues,

91
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,190
Zhizhong will be liable.

92
00:05:00,870 --> 00:05:03,360
Fang Yun is way too cunning.

93
00:05:04,177 --> 00:05:06,310
And all my efforts
to get my little weapon reinstated

94
00:05:06,310 --> 00:05:07,480
will be wasted.

95
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:11,240
This has nothing to do with us, right?

96
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,120
How is it unrelated?

97
00:05:13,870 --> 00:05:16,160
Qian Fei isn't someone
who gives up easily.

98
00:05:17,830 --> 00:05:19,040
Maybe...

99
00:05:19,066 --> 00:05:21,133
Maybe she'll investigate
all the way to Chengdu.

100
00:05:22,630 --> 00:05:24,000
To... To Chengdu?

101
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:27,680
Shanlifang only entered
East China in the past three years.

102
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:29,630
The original data from three years ago

103
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:31,430
is at their headquarters in Chengdu.

104
00:05:31,822 --> 00:05:33,870
Looks like I'll have to
make a trip to Chengdu, too.

105
00:05:35,270 --> 00:05:38,480
Boss, we're dealing with Fang Yun,

106
00:05:38,630 --> 00:05:39,680
not Shanlifang.

107
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:42,360
Shanlifang is the source of everything.

108
00:05:42,680 --> 00:05:44,310
Only by getting the original data

109
00:05:44,310 --> 00:05:45,920
can we have a real trump card.

110
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:47,680
But you don't need to go yourself.

111
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:50,000
I can send an intern there.

112
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:53,000
The evidence must be well hidden.

113
00:05:53,510 --> 00:05:55,830
How could an intern possibly find them?

114
00:05:57,950 --> 00:05:58,830
Besides,

115
00:06:01,133 --> 00:06:03,040
I'm worried
Qian Fei might get in trouble.

116
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:04,430
I need to help her.

117
00:06:06,870 --> 00:06:07,950
You're doing this for...

118
00:06:07,950 --> 00:06:09,430
For our project.

119
00:06:12,288 --> 00:06:13,160
You talk too much.

120
00:06:13,377 --> 00:06:15,444
How about this?
I don't want to argue with them.

121
00:06:15,511 --> 00:06:16,720
You... you tell them

122
00:06:16,720 --> 00:06:18,333
I went home
because I'm not feeling well.

123
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:19,488
You deal with them.

124
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:20,310
No problem.

125
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:22,720
Stalling tactics are my specialty.

126
00:06:25,244 --> 00:06:27,511
Don't forget the toilet paper
when you use the restroom.

127
00:06:40,830 --> 00:06:41,680
Zhao De.

128
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:44,630
That ended quickly...

129
00:06:44,630 --> 00:06:45,950
After our legal team reviews it...

130
00:06:45,950 --> 00:06:47,620
It has ended,
but Li Yifei isn't back yet.

131
00:06:47,630 --> 00:06:49,040
It's fine. No rush.

132
00:06:49,488 --> 00:06:50,680
Thanks for making the trip.

133
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:52,390
It's our duty.

134
00:06:52,390 --> 00:06:53,311
I won't see you out.

135
00:06:53,870 --> 00:06:54,510
Goodbye.

136
00:06:59,177 --> 00:07:00,560
Ms. Fang, you wanted to see me?

137
00:07:00,955 --> 00:07:01,950
Follow me to my office.

138
00:07:06,070 --> 00:07:07,600
I'm sure you already know.

139
00:07:08,310 --> 00:07:09,630
I used some data

140
00:07:09,933 --> 00:07:11,120
from the report you prepared

141
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,390
in today's meeting.

142
00:07:12,630 --> 00:07:13,560
Your work wasn't wasted.

143
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,310
I'll give you a bonus.

144
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:16,390
No need.

145
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:18,270
I didn't do it for a bonus.

146
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:20,030
You did it for your reinstatement

147
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:21,870
and to join Shanlifang's
IPO project team.

148
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:23,310
Yes.

149
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:25,750
Ms. Fang, I made this report

150
00:07:26,190 --> 00:07:28,240
to demonstrate my capabilities

151
00:07:28,510 --> 00:07:30,000
and to show

152
00:07:30,070 --> 00:07:32,270
the value I can bring to this company.

153
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:33,480
I know

154
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:34,920
I may have missed many chances,

155
00:07:35,390 --> 00:07:36,560
but I can guarantee

156
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:37,830
that in my future work,

157
00:07:37,888 --> 00:07:38,720
I will definitely...

158
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:39,644
Don't misunderstand.

159
00:07:41,190 --> 00:07:43,310
Using your report
doesn't mean I'm using you.

160
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:45,480
Your report did save me a lot of effort.

161
00:07:45,750 --> 00:07:47,270
But take a look yourself.

162
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:49,360
It's full of secondhand data.

163
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:50,920
Do you think I can use that

164
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:51,720
to solve problems

165
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:54,600
and skip doing my own research?

166
00:07:59,530 --> 00:08:02,000
You've probably been stuck
in back end for too long.

167
00:08:02,310 --> 00:08:04,360
You're not qualified
to join my project team yet.

168
00:08:18,244 --> 00:08:20,088
Opportunities come to those prepared.

169
00:08:22,830 --> 00:08:23,510
That's all.

170
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:28,830
You may leave now.

171
00:08:31,390 --> 00:08:32,080
Okay.

172
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:33,910
Thank you, Ms. Fang.

173
00:08:34,670 --> 00:08:35,550
Goodbye, Ms. Fang.

174
00:08:40,340 --> 00:08:42,220
(Marketing Director's Office)

175
00:08:51,550 --> 00:08:53,150
Don't get discouraged.

176
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:54,510
Have some coffee.

177
00:08:54,630 --> 00:08:55,755
It'll make you feel better.

178
00:08:56,120 --> 00:08:57,320
Who says I'm discouraged?

179
00:08:58,320 --> 00:08:59,150
Then what's with you?

180
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:01,320
I'm thinking of a solution.

181
00:09:01,390 --> 00:09:02,510
Ms. Fang said

182
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:05,270
I haven't demonstrated
my research abilities.

183
00:09:05,790 --> 00:09:06,750
Then I'll show her.

184
00:09:07,150 --> 00:09:08,200
It's good to work hard.

185
00:09:08,377 --> 00:09:09,933
Just keep your emotions in check.

186
00:09:10,670 --> 00:09:12,390
I know exactly what I need to do.

187
00:09:12,910 --> 00:09:14,200
Originally, I thought

188
00:09:14,630 --> 00:09:15,960
I could save my trump card

189
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:17,870
until after joining the project team.

190
00:09:18,790 --> 00:09:19,790
But now it seems

191
00:09:20,150 --> 00:09:22,840
I have to act immediately.

192
00:09:24,510 --> 00:09:25,080
No.

193
00:09:25,750 --> 00:09:26,870
What are you going to do?

194
00:09:27,550 --> 00:09:28,120
Go home.

195
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:31,550
Just wait and see. Bye.

196
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:46,150
(Without Shanlifang's authorization,)

197
00:09:46,550 --> 00:09:48,550
(I have no right
to conduct field research.)

198
00:09:50,390 --> 00:09:51,910
(In that case,)

199
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:54,750
(I'll have to get the original records.)

200
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:57,720
(But anyone whose data)

201
00:09:57,720 --> 00:09:59,320
(would be found to have been altered)

202
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:01,790
(would destroy it,)

203
00:10:01,870 --> 00:10:03,030
(not keep it, right?)

204
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:05,220
(Revenue Breakdown)

205
00:10:05,870 --> 00:10:07,080
(If the employee responsible)

206
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:09,222
(for auditing Shanlifang
Chengdu's internal records)

207
00:10:09,266 --> 00:10:11,840
(and the headquarters' financial
statements was smart enough)

208
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:13,600
(and wanted to protect himself...)

209
00:10:15,311 --> 00:10:16,510
(Yes, it'll only be him.)

210
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:21,630
(But he must be a key member
of the finance department.)

211
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:24,150
(Why would he give me the files?)

212
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:27,960
(Forget it.
I'll find this person first.)

213
00:10:27,970 --> 00:10:29,555
(Then I'll know how to deal with him.)

214
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:39,150
Limited edition.

215
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:40,600
That's right.

216
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:43,390
Knowing Mr. Liao likes golf,

217
00:10:43,550 --> 00:10:46,120
so I asked a friend overseas
to look for it for ages.

218
00:10:46,155 --> 00:10:47,300
I got it especially for you.

219
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,240
It took a lot of effort.

220
00:10:51,030 --> 00:10:51,720
I like it.

221
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:53,360
Glad you do.

222
00:10:55,150 --> 00:10:55,790
Yifei.

223
00:10:57,510 --> 00:10:59,200
What? Last time we met,

224
00:10:59,390 --> 00:11:01,080
you kept calling me Chairman Liao.

225
00:11:01,870 --> 00:11:04,600
This time, it's not for work?

226
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:05,960
Of course.

227
00:11:06,530 --> 00:11:07,930
Your birthday is coming up.

228
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,750
As a junior, I had to show my respect.

229
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:10,670
Right?

230
00:11:12,630 --> 00:11:14,670
You can give gifts on the actual day.

231
00:11:14,910 --> 00:11:16,480
You're in quite a hurry.

232
00:11:17,577 --> 00:11:18,870
I was just about to tell you.

233
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,266
I'm going to Chengdu tomorrow.

234
00:11:20,910 --> 00:11:22,510
I'm worried that I won't make it

235
00:11:22,550 --> 00:11:23,440
to your birthday party.

236
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:26,120
You're going to Chengdu?

237
00:11:28,390 --> 00:11:29,440
You're currently

238
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:31,150
the head of our IPO project.

239
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:33,030
How can you travel at a time like this?

240
00:11:33,390 --> 00:11:34,600
Here's the thing, Mr. Liao.

241
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:37,600
There's a small
international academic forum

242
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:38,630
being held in Chengdu.

243
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:40,750
A professor I know was invited,

244
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:42,120
and he asked me to join him.

245
00:11:42,670 --> 00:11:44,120
I thought it would be a chance

246
00:11:44,390 --> 00:11:46,550
to properly introduce
Shanlifang at the forum.

247
00:11:46,644 --> 00:11:48,288
Although there won't be media coverage,

248
00:11:48,360 --> 00:11:50,030
we can still build momentum

249
00:11:50,150 --> 00:11:52,022
for Shanlifang's listing
in academic circles.

250
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:53,080
So I said yes.

251
00:11:54,790 --> 00:11:57,030
Build momentum without media coverage?

252
00:11:57,960 --> 00:11:59,510
These finance scholars

253
00:11:59,670 --> 00:12:01,240
are all top experts in the industry.

254
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:02,910
You understand that.

255
00:12:05,390 --> 00:12:05,960
Good.

256
00:12:07,155 --> 00:12:08,888
It's rare to see
such initiative from you.

257
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:11,510
Yifei.

258
00:12:12,270 --> 00:12:13,550
If you need any support,

259
00:12:13,960 --> 00:12:15,120
just say the word.

260
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,480
I wouldn't call it support,

261
00:12:21,390 --> 00:12:22,510
but I do have one concern.

262
00:12:25,133 --> 00:12:26,270
Stop beating around the bush.

263
00:12:26,910 --> 00:12:28,000
Just say it.

264
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:29,390
Alright, I'll be direct.

265
00:12:30,550 --> 00:12:33,270
Since it's an academic forum,

266
00:12:34,030 --> 00:12:36,200
the topics covered will be very broad.

267
00:12:36,670 --> 00:12:39,360
But the data I currently have

268
00:12:39,670 --> 00:12:41,270
isn't enough to support my arguments.

269
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:42,320
If I could also

270
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:43,600
get the data

271
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:46,080
from Shanlifang's Chengdu partners
from three years ago,

272
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:47,720
that would be a huge help.

273
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:02,840
So you're saying

274
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:05,390
you need my authorization

275
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:07,390
to represent Shanlifang

276
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:10,630
and communicate
with the partners in Chengdu,

277
00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:11,320
right?

278
00:13:13,080 --> 00:13:13,510
Yes.

279
00:13:13,550 --> 00:13:15,750
If it's convenient
for you to authorize me,

280
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:17,440
the results would be better.

281
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:19,150
But if you're worried...

282
00:13:20,550 --> 00:13:21,440
That's fine, too.

283
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:22,750
It... It's no big deal.

284
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:28,360
Listen to yourself.
What would I be worried about?

285
00:13:28,550 --> 00:13:29,480
It's just authorization.

286
00:13:30,510 --> 00:13:32,320
I'll have my secretary
prepare it shortly.

287
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:34,360
Yifei.

288
00:13:35,630 --> 00:13:36,440
Not only that,

289
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:41,240
I'll give you
the contact details of all the partners.

290
00:13:41,910 --> 00:13:42,630
Kid.

291
00:13:43,670 --> 00:13:45,960
Take that golf club and swing boldly.

292
00:13:46,440 --> 00:13:47,870
That's great, Mr. Liao.

293
00:13:48,177 --> 00:13:49,288
Thank you, Chairman Liao.

294
00:13:49,555 --> 00:13:50,360
There you go again.

295
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:52,630
Didn't we agree to call me
Mr. Liao in private?

296
00:13:52,870 --> 00:13:54,360
Yes. Thank you, Mr. Liao.

297
00:13:55,020 --> 00:13:56,700
(Group News)

298
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:01,200
This corporate news related to finance

299
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:03,480
should've been written
by professional finance staff.

300
00:14:04,390 --> 00:14:05,870
Why isn't there a single byline?

301
00:14:09,620 --> 00:14:14,220
(We Empowered the Future Together.
2018 Company Annual Dinner Report)

302
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:19,200
Annual dinner...

303
00:14:19,550 --> 00:14:21,600
From three years ago?

304
00:14:23,980 --> 00:14:27,820
(Employee of the Year:
Finance Department, Xin You)

305
00:14:48,550 --> 00:14:50,360
Flying would be more efficient.

306
00:14:51,910 --> 00:14:52,910
As for the return trip,

307
00:14:53,790 --> 00:14:55,200
I'll take a hard seat to save money.

308
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:57,150
I can write on the way.

309
00:14:57,260 --> 00:14:58,380
(Shanghai to Chengdu, Booking)

310
00:14:58,460 --> 00:14:59,460
(Passenger Information)

311
00:15:04,860 --> 00:15:07,060
(Chengdu to Shanghai, Hard Seat)

312
00:15:09,380 --> 00:15:12,220
(Hotel)

313
00:15:14,150 --> 00:15:14,600
This...

314
00:15:15,030 --> 00:15:17,200
Why is the accommodation so expensive?

315
00:15:25,840 --> 00:15:27,320
My dad's birthday is next week.

316
00:15:27,790 --> 00:15:29,360
We're having a small banquet.

317
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:30,390
You should come.

318
00:15:31,550 --> 00:15:31,960
Sure.

319
00:15:32,790 --> 00:15:34,133
Why aren't you surprised at all?

320
00:15:34,488 --> 00:15:35,440
Did you already know?

321
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:37,550
As a subordinate,

322
00:15:37,550 --> 00:15:39,760
of course, I know
the chairman's birthday is coming up.

323
00:15:39,770 --> 00:15:41,155
I've even prepared a gift for him.

324
00:15:41,200 --> 00:15:41,960
What gift?

325
00:15:42,688 --> 00:15:44,200
I bought him some supplements.

326
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:45,750
Supplements?

327
00:15:46,720 --> 00:15:48,550
My dad hates receiving supplements.

328
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:50,750
It's basically saying
he's old to his face.

329
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:54,150
Then what does he like?

330
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:56,200
Don't worry about that.

331
00:15:56,288 --> 00:15:57,444
I'll prepare it for you.

332
00:15:58,133 --> 00:15:59,150
Isn't that inappropriate?

333
00:15:59,422 --> 00:16:00,733
What's inappropriate about it?

334
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:02,270
Look at you. You've lost weight.

335
00:16:02,622 --> 00:16:04,422
You work overtime
and stay up late every day.

336
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:05,750
It's hard enough just to see you.

337
00:16:07,550 --> 00:16:09,390
I just took over this job here.

338
00:16:10,088 --> 00:16:11,911
There are still many things to sort out.

339
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:15,510
Actually, don't worry too much

340
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:17,200
about work.

341
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:21,510
You only need to do one thing well.

342
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:23,080
Treat me well.

343
00:16:46,150 --> 00:16:48,240
Li Yifei, I'm going out for a while.

344
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:49,550
I'll be back in a week at most.

345
00:16:49,630 --> 00:16:50,870
Don't make a mess of the house.

346
00:16:51,030 --> 00:16:51,960
If you don't cook,

347
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:53,670
remember to turn off the gas valve.

348
00:16:54,622 --> 00:16:55,666
What are you going for?

349
00:16:56,360 --> 00:16:57,360
To clear my head.

350
00:17:23,960 --> 00:17:25,400
Miss, excuse me.

351
00:17:27,550 --> 00:17:28,000
You...

352
00:17:28,355 --> 00:17:29,310
Why are you here?

353
00:17:29,310 --> 00:17:30,510
Weren't you still asleep?

354
00:17:30,510 --> 00:17:31,800
I'm on a business trip today.

355
00:17:33,310 --> 00:17:34,680
You're going to Chengdu, too?

356
00:17:37,070 --> 00:17:39,350
So you're going
to Chengdu to clear your head.

357
00:17:41,110 --> 00:17:41,750
Yeah.

358
00:17:43,640 --> 00:17:44,830
What a coincidence.

359
00:17:45,533 --> 00:17:47,070
Can you get behind me in line now?

360
00:17:47,510 --> 00:17:48,270
Sorry.

361
00:17:48,333 --> 00:17:49,480
I'm flying business class.

362
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:51,000
We're not even at the same counter.

363
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:54,400
Then go to your business class counter.
Why come here?

364
00:17:54,720 --> 00:17:55,510
I just wanted you

365
00:17:55,510 --> 00:17:56,800
to pretend to be my secretary

366
00:17:56,880 --> 00:17:58,577
so that I can bring you
into business class.

367
00:17:58,640 --> 00:17:59,790
Pretend to be your secretary?

368
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:01,550
Am I crazy, or are you crazy?

369
00:18:03,644 --> 00:18:05,030
Why are you going to Chengdu?

370
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:06,888
Are you trying to
investigate Shanlifang?

371
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:11,680
You want to come with me?

372
00:18:14,110 --> 00:18:15,830
Why would I want to go with you?

373
00:18:17,350 --> 00:18:19,350
I'm not even
part of your project team.

374
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:25,000
The reason you're going to Chengdu

375
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:26,480
is that you saw

376
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:28,200
the research report I gave Ms. Fang.

377
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,066
Only the financial data

378
00:18:29,070 --> 00:18:31,570
before Shanlifang's headquarters
moved to East China had issues.

379
00:18:31,688 --> 00:18:32,480
That's why

380
00:18:32,480 --> 00:18:34,640
you're going to Chengdu
to find the original data, right?

381
00:18:35,270 --> 00:18:38,109
If you hadn't seen my report,
you wouldn't have noticed the problem.

382
00:18:38,110 --> 00:18:39,350
I actually helped you.

383
00:18:40,244 --> 00:18:41,920
You're giving yourself too much credit.

384
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:45,480
I discovered Shanlifang's issues
a long time ago.

385
00:18:46,030 --> 00:18:46,790
Besides,

386
00:18:47,270 --> 00:18:49,440
I helped you finish that report.

387
00:18:49,510 --> 00:18:50,070
Don't forget.

388
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:53,790
Even you discovered that it has issues.

389
00:18:54,590 --> 00:18:55,550
Logically speaking,

390
00:18:55,720 --> 00:18:57,680
Ms. Fang couldn't know nothing about it.

391
00:18:57,710 --> 00:18:59,590
Don't you think
the attitude Ms. Fang showed...

392
00:18:59,590 --> 00:19:00,000
Exactly.

393
00:19:00,590 --> 00:19:02,310
Don't you think her attitude is strange?

394
00:19:02,920 --> 00:19:03,510
Don't you think

395
00:19:03,510 --> 00:19:05,390
this question
is worth thinking about carefully?

396
00:19:06,550 --> 00:19:07,440
Alright, stop thinking.

397
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:09,177
Let's go.
I'll take you to business class.

398
00:19:10,355 --> 00:19:12,030
You can bring someone
into business class?

399
00:19:12,160 --> 00:19:13,030
What do you think?

400
00:19:18,070 --> 00:19:19,110
Yes, okay.

401
00:19:19,750 --> 00:19:20,790
Then it's settled.

402
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:23,750
Come in.

403
00:19:23,820 --> 00:19:26,420
(Marketing Director's Office)

404
00:19:28,240 --> 00:19:29,030
Ms. Fang.

405
00:19:29,111 --> 00:19:30,440
Li Yifei has gone to Chengdu.

406
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:35,510
He's heading straight
for Shanlifang's headquarters.

407
00:19:37,310 --> 00:19:39,400
Looks like pushing him yesterday worked.

408
00:19:41,440 --> 00:19:42,920
You mean that agreement

409
00:19:42,920 --> 00:19:44,350
was meant to force him

410
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:46,070
to investigate Shanlifang's books?

411
00:19:46,733 --> 00:19:48,790
There must be problems
with Shanlifang's accounts.

412
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:50,920
Tell me,

413
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:53,110
if we hold these unclear accounts,

414
00:19:53,510 --> 00:19:55,030
as the sponsor,

415
00:19:55,030 --> 00:19:57,444
won't we be implicated when things
come to light in the future?

416
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:01,110
But didn't you say

417
00:20:01,510 --> 00:20:03,440
not to touch Qian Fei's report

418
00:20:03,550 --> 00:20:04,830
and not to keep investigating?

419
00:20:05,711 --> 00:20:06,960
Did I tell you to investigate?

420
00:20:08,333 --> 00:20:10,240
Did I tell
anyone from Hejing to investigate?

421
00:20:11,920 --> 00:20:13,680
What's the purpose
of falsifying accounts?

422
00:20:15,590 --> 00:20:16,830
It's to make money.

423
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,310
But if we investigate their books,

424
00:20:19,422 --> 00:20:21,288
aren't we cutting off
their source of income?

425
00:20:23,110 --> 00:20:24,160
Tell me,

426
00:20:24,880 --> 00:20:26,750
will Liao Jinshan let it go

427
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:29,070
if Shanlifang suffers losses?

428
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:31,160
Got it.

429
00:20:31,577 --> 00:20:33,750
If we don't investigate,
we might take the blame later.

430
00:20:34,110 --> 00:20:35,310
If we investigate personally,

431
00:20:36,030 --> 00:20:37,200
we'll offend Shanlifang.

432
00:20:37,510 --> 00:20:38,830
So the best approach

433
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:40,350
is to have someone else

434
00:20:40,422 --> 00:20:41,955
stir up this hornet's nest for us.

435
00:20:44,310 --> 00:20:45,200
If Zhizhong

436
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:47,830
is forced out because of this,

437
00:20:50,070 --> 00:20:52,350
Hejing will become the sole underwriter.

438
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:56,640
That's killing
three birds with one stone.

439
00:20:58,640 --> 00:21:00,920
What should we do next?

440
00:21:01,920 --> 00:21:02,880
Wait and see.

441
00:21:06,310 --> 00:21:06,920
Okay.

442
00:21:07,790 --> 00:21:08,510
I'll leave now.

443
00:21:08,510 --> 00:21:12,940
(Hejing Securities Co., Ltd.)

444
00:21:21,270 --> 00:21:22,070
Hello, sir.

445
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:24,680
May I ask if you're traveling alone?

446
00:21:25,590 --> 00:21:26,200
Why?

447
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:27,680
You see, there's a gentleman

448
00:21:27,680 --> 00:21:29,070
who'd like to switch seats with you.

449
00:21:29,310 --> 00:21:31,550
His seat is in business class up front.

450
00:21:31,550 --> 00:21:32,740
Would that be okay with you?

451
00:21:32,750 --> 00:21:33,160
Sure.

452
00:21:33,480 --> 00:21:33,960
Great.

453
00:21:40,240 --> 00:21:41,030
Thank you.

454
00:21:53,555 --> 00:21:55,790
Why aren't you sitting
in your plush business-class seat

455
00:21:55,920 --> 00:21:57,160
and coming to economy class?

456
00:21:57,680 --> 00:21:59,030
I came to check on you.

457
00:22:00,640 --> 00:22:02,310
I'm just looking for
a good show to watch.

458
00:22:03,350 --> 00:22:04,440
Did you find one?

459
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:05,720
Not yet.

460
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:07,110
Sure.

461
00:22:10,177 --> 00:22:12,355
What are you doing?
Why are you plugging in a USB?

462
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:14,960
Stop watching shows. Study instead.

463
00:22:15,020 --> 00:22:16,420
(Enter Password)

464
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:18,510
These are my personal notes

465
00:22:18,510 --> 00:22:19,590
from years of project work.

466
00:22:20,270 --> 00:22:21,000
Study them well.

467
00:22:22,720 --> 00:22:23,590
Acting mature again.

468
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:24,880
Fine. Give it back then.

469
00:22:25,640 --> 00:22:26,400
Don't move.

470
00:22:26,550 --> 00:22:27,733
Finger-Snapping Technique.

471
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:29,720
You're childish.

472
00:22:31,550 --> 00:22:32,680
Let's see how smart you are.

473
00:22:32,830 --> 00:22:34,310
Who knows if you can master it?

474
00:22:35,444 --> 00:22:37,440
I'm telling you.
I can't guarantee anything else,

475
00:22:37,440 --> 00:22:39,700
but there's nothing I can't learn
when it comes to learning.

476
00:22:39,711 --> 00:22:41,240
Okay. Impressive.

477
00:22:44,660 --> 00:22:48,820
(Life in Investment Banking)

478
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:53,030
It's a great manual.

479
00:22:56,750 --> 00:22:57,590
Tell me.

480
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:59,240
You're teaching me everything.

481
00:22:59,240 --> 00:23:00,480
What are you after?

482
00:23:09,550 --> 00:23:10,480
I get it.

483
00:23:10,790 --> 00:23:12,640
Once we arrive in Chengdu,

484
00:23:12,790 --> 00:23:14,030
you want me to help you

485
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:16,044
investigate Shanlifang's
early financial data.

486
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:17,160
You said that yourself.

487
00:23:17,550 --> 00:23:18,440
I didn't say it,

488
00:23:19,720 --> 00:23:20,640
but that works, too.

489
00:23:22,270 --> 00:23:23,880
Since you want to be with me so much,

490
00:23:24,160 --> 00:23:24,590
I...

491
00:23:24,790 --> 00:23:25,830
I don't.

492
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:27,440
I'm going there for vacation.

493
00:23:31,350 --> 00:23:32,070
Alright.

494
00:23:32,070 --> 00:23:33,880
I'll cook for you every day
when we get back.

495
00:23:33,911 --> 00:23:35,444
Stir-fried eggplant and braised pork.

496
00:23:36,266 --> 00:23:36,960
How about this?

497
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:39,270
I'll give you two hours
to think about it.

498
00:23:39,480 --> 00:23:40,550
Once we land in Chengdu,

499
00:23:40,600 --> 00:23:41,555
give me your answer.

500
00:23:43,590 --> 00:23:44,350
Study hard.

501
00:23:45,270 --> 00:23:47,160
I need some rest.

502
00:23:56,310 --> 00:23:57,510
Study hard.

503
00:23:59,911 --> 00:24:01,244
You scared me to death.

504
00:24:05,030 --> 00:24:06,750
Soup's here.

505
00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:08,720
Alright, stop playing your phone.

506
00:24:08,880 --> 00:24:09,720
It's so fun.

507
00:24:09,720 --> 00:24:10,400
Time to eat.

508
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:11,750
Just a second. I'm almost done.

509
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:13,790
I... I may not know how to play,

510
00:24:13,790 --> 00:24:15,000
but seeing Team China win

511
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:16,200
makes me excited.

512
00:24:17,440 --> 00:24:18,960
My blood is pumping.

513
00:24:19,110 --> 00:24:20,240
Mom, don't get too excited.

514
00:24:20,400 --> 00:24:21,440
No matter how much I play,

515
00:24:21,640 --> 00:24:22,920
I won't become a champion.

516
00:24:23,070 --> 00:24:24,370
Don't put so much pressure on me.

517
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:26,750
Who's putting pressure on you? Jeez.

518
00:24:27,030 --> 00:24:28,680
What pressure? Be confident.

519
00:24:29,480 --> 00:24:31,000
Well... When you

520
00:24:31,240 --> 00:24:32,550
become a champion one day,

521
00:24:32,590 --> 00:24:33,830
I will be overjoyed.

522
00:24:35,350 --> 00:24:37,400
Alright, from now on,

523
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:38,720
I won't

524
00:24:39,070 --> 00:24:40,030
oppose gaming anymore.

525
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:40,711
I support it.

526
00:24:42,920 --> 00:24:44,790
Here.

527
00:24:44,977 --> 00:24:46,550
Have a drumstick for extra nutrition.

528
00:24:46,550 --> 00:24:47,640
Training keeps you busy.

529
00:24:49,030 --> 00:24:50,750
Have a drumstick for extra nutrition.

530
00:24:50,790 --> 00:24:52,222
Dad, I haven't even eaten much,

531
00:24:52,266 --> 00:24:54,030
but I'm already full
from watching you two.

532
00:24:55,750 --> 00:24:56,750
You're single.

533
00:24:56,750 --> 00:24:58,488
You need to accept
your fate as a single.

534
00:24:58,720 --> 00:25:00,160
You can't even find a girlfriend.

535
00:25:00,244 --> 00:25:02,488
And you're stopping me and your mom
from showing affection.

536
00:25:02,510 --> 00:25:03,830
You can do it, too.

537
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:04,680
Yeah.

538
00:25:04,866 --> 00:25:06,377
You need someone to show affection to.

539
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:07,750
Who would you show it to?

540
00:25:07,750 --> 00:25:09,550
How can you show affection
when you're single?

541
00:25:09,550 --> 00:25:10,160
Exactly.

542
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:11,000
Bring someone home

543
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:12,110
and show us.

544
00:25:16,830 --> 00:25:17,830
Jun.

545
00:25:18,160 --> 00:25:19,240
You're 30 already.

546
00:25:19,510 --> 00:25:20,200
Mom.

547
00:25:20,640 --> 00:25:22,270
Your son is only 26.

548
00:25:22,355 --> 00:25:24,640
What about nominal age?
Add two years, and that's 28, right?

549
00:25:24,640 --> 00:25:25,550
You're almost 30 anyway.

550
00:25:25,550 --> 00:25:26,270
That's right.

551
00:25:26,550 --> 00:25:27,480
Aren't you nearing 30?

552
00:25:32,590 --> 00:25:33,400
Well...

553
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:36,070
You could take a look

554
00:25:36,270 --> 00:25:37,680
at our leader's daughter.

555
00:25:37,777 --> 00:25:38,750
